de.esoco.lib.model

Interface FilterableDataModel<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataModel<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public interface FilterableDataModel<T>
extends DataModel<T>
    An extended data model that allows to filter the contained data elements by setting filter constraints for element fields.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static char CONSTRAINT_AND_PREFIX
      The prefix character for constraints that should be combined with a logical AND.
      static java.lang.String CONSTRAINT_COMPARISON_CHARS
      The possible comparison characters for constraints (≠,≤,≥: ≠,≤,≥). '~' means "almost equal" and is used for fuzzy searches. '#' means "element of' and can be followed by a comma-separated list of values.

      • setFilter

        void setFilter(java.lang.String sFieldId,
               java.lang.String sFilter)
        Sets the filter for a certain field. If the filter value is NULL an existing constraint for the given field will be removed. The filter will be concatenated with a logical AND expression if the first character is CONSTRAINT_AND_PREFIX and with a logical OR if it is CONSTRAINT_OR_PREFIX.

        It is possible to set multiple filter constraints on a field by concatenating them with a CONSTRAINT_SEPARATOR in between. Any occurrences of the separator string in a constraint must therefore be escaped by replacing them with the CONSTRAINT_SEPARATOR_ESCAPE.

        If the first character of the filter is one of the characters in the constant CONSTRAINT_COMPARISON_CHARS the corresponding comparison will be applied to the filter value that follows after the character. If omitted an equals comparison will be used.

        Besides simple text the filter value may contain expressions, placeholders, and wildcards to allow searches that cover a range of values as shown below. The wildcard characters '*' and '?' can be combined. Attention: not all implementations may support value expressions, some may even only support simple string matching.

        • <[Value]: Matches all values that are less than the given value
        • >[Value]: Matches all values that are greater than the given value
        • [Value]*: Matches any string that starts with the given value.
        • *[Value]: Matches any string that ends with the given value.
        • *[Value]*: Matches any string that contains the given value.
        • [Va]?[ue]: The question mark is a wildcard for an arbitrary character; multiple question marks are allowed.
        • ![Value]: Matches any string that does NOT match the given value. The value may contain wildcard characters.
        Parameters:
        sFieldId - The ID of the data field to set the filter for
        sFilter - The filter value or NULL to remove a filter

      • setFilters

        void setFilters(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> rFilters)
        Sets the filters of this model. This will remove any existing filters.
        Parameters:
        rFilters - A mapping from field ID strings to filter strings
